  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Then Hezekiah answered and said,.... Or proceeded to say, as follows: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "now ye have consecrated yourselves unto the Lord; having entered anew on the performance of their office, filling their hands with sacrifices, as the words signify: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "come near, and bring sacrifices and thank offerings into the house of the Lord; which the people were to put into their hands to offer for them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the congregation brought in sacrifices and thank offerings; peace offerings, part of which the offerers had to feast on with their friends so expressing their joy and thankfulness on this occasion: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and as many as were of a free heart burnt offerings; of which they had no share, but were wholly the Lord's; and which was a greater proof of their liberality, and so of their sincere and cordial thankfulness. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and as many as were of a free heart burnt offerings; of which they had no share, but were wholly the Lord's; and which was a greater proof of their liberality, and so of their sincere and cordial thankfulness. ",
